posts.body: I hope /delicious/ and /animu/ come back, but otherwise this is a rather dark period for us. Might never recover.
While I'm here, I may as well ask how do I delete zeronet cache? Where is it stored? Not 100% sure how it works but apparently the more I browse the more space I take up.

>>554a3480-d04c-4aee-bb09-b0280c2abdd3
Translation: 8chan is dead forever and in due time even Zeronet will pay the price for harboring us. I rather not have to go back to 4chan's Japanese learning threads. Seconding >>06c75b55-e57e-4464-957a-88db3540cb5a on wanting /delicious/ back. Those request threads were hopping and I don't see any other imageboard allowing something like that. Hell, do the drawfags even know about the bunker?!

>>0734ecd9-ff3e-406d-b26c-a6fb5ca5ce52
Got anything to refute said niggerpilling? We're in the end times of absolute anonymity, short of migrating to fucking TOR.

Oh thank God, I was waiting for this thread to come back. Waiting on /animu/, /delicious/, and /hgg/ to get back up to speed now.

>>73957f21-123b-4f0f-9a97-8411127f8279
Oh shit, is /hebe/ gonna come back with a vengeance?
Once fully seeded, do the files go to any folder in particular, or do you have to save them manually?

>>098eae96-b3ef-41fa-8b54-e129a063fa1b
Wish Windows allows folders to be organized by size. Seems I have a lot of folders with 2 .json files, very few having thumbnails and fewer still with src subfolders with the actual pics. I get the feeling this is gonna get very unmanageable very quickly (I already have about 300MB cached) so at least this way I can delete individual folders manually (assuming it doesn't mess anything up).

In short, thank you.
